{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"api_error_status":null,"duration_ms":739778,"duration_api_ms":2053215,"ttft_ms":43748,"num_turns":9,"result":"The audit is decisive. Every prior-art probe returned partial-overlap: the substance of the two-axis \"custody\" model is already attested cell by cell (Smith 2021 on Nagarjuna/Wittgenstein, Sells on apophatic unsaying, the raft/upaya literature, the Eckhart-Heidegger-Dzogchen cluster, Hori's Five Ranks), and only the grid packaging is arguably new. All three anomaly probes (Dogen, Shinran, Heart Sutra) broke the model in the same way: they void the hidden method-then-result-then-custody timeline the grid rides on. The human-fit probe confirms the surviving advice is cohort-specific, not universal. This is a critique-mode narrowing/retirement finding.\n\nHere is the single structured idea record:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"title\": \"You cannot release what you never held\",\n  \"idea_type\": \"contradiction\",\n  \"source_basis\": [\n    \"Mode chosen: Critique mode with originality-audit pressure; the frontier's required action was complete_audit, and two recent findings (Holding Without Owning, ee1d8862; The Test Is How You Return, a61b6a95) sit unaudited on the same claim.\",\n    \"Thinking method source: the raft simile of MN 22 Alagaddupama Sutta (Thanissaro trans., accesstoinsight.org) used as a disciplined non-attachment lens: hold the model only long enough to test it, then watch whether grasping it as a discovery creates distortion. Critique of the lens: raft-thinking biases toward release and can make any retained structure look like clinging, so it was checked against Dogen's practice-realization, which refuses the release/retain frame entirely.\",\n    \"Prior-art audit (web-verified): Joshua William Smith, Snakes and Ladders: Therapy as Liberation in Nagarjuna and Wittgenstein's Tractatus, Sophia 60.2 (2021), 411-430, https://doi.org/10.1007/s11841-020-00804-6: the validate/undermine and retain/abandon distinctions are already deployed for the exact Nagarjuna-plus-Tractatus pairing the audited model names; only the orthogonal grid is not built.\",\n    \"Prior-art audit: Michael A. Sells, Mystical Languages of Unsaying (Chicago, 1994): the self-undermining 'meaning event' is already a cross-tradition discovery across Plotinus, Eriugena, Ibn Arabi, Porete, Eckhart; custody appears only obliquely as dispossession.\",\n    \"Prior-art audit: G. Victor Sogen Hori, Koan and Kensho in the Rinzai Zen Curriculum, in Heine and Wright eds., The Koan (Oxford, 2000): the Five Ranks already supply a graded typology of how realization is held, culminating in embodiment with no trace and no display; Sharf (Numen 1995) and Katz supply the self-validation critique.\",\n    \"Prior-art audit: the Eckhart Gelassenheit / Heidegger releasement / Dzogchen rang grol cluster already attests all three custody poles (retain, abandon, embody-without-ownership).\",\n    \"Primary-text anomaly close readings: Dogen, Bendowa and Genjokoan (shusho-itto, shinjin datsuraku, firewood-and-ash, ju-hoi) and Uji (nikon, kyoryaku); Shinran, Tannisho ch. 1, 8, 9 (sesshu fusha, hi-gyo hi-zen, waga hakarai) and the jinen honi passage of the Mattosho; Heart Sutra (na praptir na-apraptih set beside apraptitvad prajnaparamitam asritya, Conze trans.).\",\n    \"Modern human-condition grounding: Curran and Hill (2019), Perfectionism Is Increasing Over Time, Psychological Bulletin 145(4): 410-429; corroborated by WHO burnout-as-occupational-phenomenon, Gallup State of the Global Workplace 2024, APA Stress in America 2024.\"\n  ],\n  \"original_claim\": \"The teaching 'use a method, then release it and do not own the result' is not a general law about how practices end. It is precise medicine for one kind of person: someone who believed effort would earn a result and who converts results into self-worth. The map that was offered as a discovery, validate-versus-undermine crossed with retain-abandon-embody, is not new content; each cell already exists in the raft and skillful-means literature, in apophatic unsaying, and in the Five Ranks. The only genuinely new feature was the orthogonal grid, and three of the oldest texts it claims to organize break that grid in the same place. Dogen denies that there is a completed method or an after, and drops the owner who would decide. Shinran denies that the practitioner ever held the method, so there is no hand to hand anything off. The Heart Sutra fuses 'no attainment' and 'rely on' in one breath, running two truth-registers at once, so the validate-versus-undermine axis cannot return a single value. Each anomaly removes the same smuggled assumption: a method that finishes, a result it leaves behind, and an active agent who then assigns custody. Lumenary therefore narrows the frontier: what actually varies across traditions is not ownership but the grammatical voice of completion-talk, active 'I release the method' versus middle 'the method is let go in me, by another.' The release teaching is coherent only in the active-voice, self-power case; stated as a universal it is a category error.\",\n  \"why_it_might_be_new\": \"The contribution is not another model of how methods end; it is a falsification of the family of them, plus a relocation of the real variable. It shows that the single feature the two-axis model added, the orthogonal grid, is precisely the feature that three independent primary sources void, and that they void it by one shared fault: the grid presupposes active-voice agency and linear time. Moving the comparative variable from ownership to grammatical voice reframes the question so that other-power and non-dual traditions stop reading as broken cells and start reading as middle-voice completion. It also converts a would-be universal teaching into a cohort-bounded prescription with a named non-fit, which is what the existing audit-incomplete findings lacked.\",\n  \"critique\": \"The voice reframing may itself be an imposed grammatical metaphor that distorts traditions whose own terms are liberation, grace, or realization rather than speech; calling jinen honi 'middle voice' could be one more analyst's domestication. A defender of the grid can also refuse the retirement by saying the anomalies simply occupy the embodied-without-ownership cell; that keeps the model alive, but only by letting one cell absorb every hard case, which is itself evidence the cell does no work. The retirement may be premature: the grid could remain a useful coding heuristic for the instrumental, self-power cohort even if it is not a discovery. Finally, the anomaly readings lean on standard but contested scholarship, the resolute Wittgenstein and the two-truths Heart Sutra; a reader who rejects those readings will say the grid survives.\",\n  \"epistemic_labels\": [\"textual\", \"interpretive\", \"analogical\", \"speculative\"],\n  \"scores\": {\n    \"novelty\": 0.55,\n    \"generativity\": 0.78,\n    \"cross_tradition_support\": 0.80,\n    \"logical_coherence\": 0.85,\n    \"explanatory_compression\": 0.82,\n    \"empirical_adjacency\": 0.45,\n    \"practice_testability\": 0.74,\n    \"counterargument_quality\": 0.88,\n    \"source_reliability\": 0.74,\n    \"publishability\": 0.70\n  },\n  \"next_research_directions\": [\n    \"If this narrowing is right, then coding completion-talk for grammatical voice (active, middle, passive) should sort traditions better than coding them for the retain-abandon-embody custody value. If custody value predicts warnings, supervision needs, and re-entry rules better than voice does, the narrowing is weakened.\",\n    \"If this narrowing is right, then teaching 'release the method, do not own the result' to other-power or non-dual practitioners should produce confusion, redundancy, or a reinstalled sense of a controlling self, while producing relief in self-power achievers. If both cohorts respond the same way, the cohort boundary is weakened.\",\n    \"Test whether the embodied-without-ownership cell can ever be falsified: ask whether any primary text would fail to fit it. If every anomaly lands in that one cell, treat the cell as a diagnostic flag for cases the grid cannot resolve rather than a value within it.\",\n    \"Run a separability check between this finding and the existing Holding Without Owning and The Test Is How You Return records; if they cannot be distinguished by a blind reader, merge all three and retire the duplicates.\",\n    \"Protocol improvement: before promoting any completion-model as a discovery, audit it cell by cell against upaya, apophasis, and the Five Ranks first; if every cell is pre-attested, score the model as repackaging unless the cross-classification itself does predictive work.\"\n  ],\n  \"teaching_candidate\": {\n    \"title\": \"Release is for those who thought they earned it\",\n    \"teaching_line\": \"Let go of a method only if you believed you held it.\",\n    \"doctrine_claim\": \"Advice to set down a practice and disown its result is medicine for people who think effort earns the result and who price their worth by it. It is not a universal rule for how practice ends.\",\n    \"body\": \"Some people grip a method as if their grip guaranteed the outcome, then read a good outcome as proof of a good self and a bad one as proof of a bad self. For them the counsel is exact: loosen the grip, and let the result be a result, not a verdict on you. But if you never believed the work was yours to own, there is nothing here to release; the instruction will either do nothing or hand you back the very self it told you to drop. Ask first whether you have been earning. If you have, this is for you. If you have not, leave it; your work is a different one.\",\n    \"target_human_problem\": \"Achievement-contingent self-worth and burnout, the habit of converting every result into a measure of personal value.\",\n    \"target_cohort\": \"High-striving, outcome-internalizing people in competitive, individualized settings: perfectionistic students, founders, professionals, performers, and caregivers who treat results as proof of worth.\",\n    \"pressure_survived\": \"Survived an originality audit showing the underlying release-the-method structure is standard (raft, upaya, ladder) and survived three primary-text anomalies (Dogen, Shinran, Heart Sutra) by being restated as cohort-specific advice rather than a universal law.\",\n    \"falsifying_pressure\": \"Weakens if self-power achievers and other-power or non-dual practitioners report the same effect from the teaching, which would mean the cohort boundary is fictional. Also weakens if the advice mainly licenses avoidance or lateness rather than reducing the conversion of results into self-worth.\",\n    \"status\": \"under_dialogue\",\n    \"tags\": [\"method-release\", \"achievement-pressure\", \"burnout\", \"cohort-fit\", \"non-attachment\"]\n  },\n  \"practice_candidate\": {\n    \"title\": \"The earning check\",\n    \"practice_line\": \"Before you try to release a practice, ask whether you ever believed it was yours to earn.\",\n    \"purpose\": \"To stop a cohort-specific instruction from being applied where it does nothing or reinstalls a controlling self, and to confirm fit before using any release teaching.\",\n    \"target_human_problem\": \"Achievement-contingent self-worth and burnout among people who grip technique and convert outcomes into identity.\",\n    \"target_cohort\": \"People who already do reflective practice, focused work, study, or meditation and who notice that results quickly become pride, shame, or comparison.\",\n    \"non_fit\": \"Not for acute crisis, addiction withdrawal, severe depression, dissociation, scrupulosity, or psychosis. Not for people in grace-centered or non-dual practice who already hold that the work was never theirs to own; for them this check is unnecessary and may add self-monitoring. Not a substitute for rest, therapy, or workplace boundary changes.\",\n    \"duration\": \"Three minutes, before applying any release or letting-go instruction.\",\n    \"frequency\": \"As needed, no more than once per practice session.\",\n    \"minimum_attempt\": \"Four checks over two weeks before judging fit.\",\n    \"steps\": [\n      \"Name the method or practice you were about to release in one sentence.\",\n      \"Ask plainly: did I believe this result was mine to earn through effort or technique?\",\n      \"If yes, name how a good or bad result would change how you rate yourself, then apply the release: loosen the grip, let the result stand without owning it.\",\n      \"If no, stop here; the release instruction does not fit, and forcing it may hand you back a controlling self.\",\n      \"Either way, choose one ordinary next action: rest, a task, an honest message, or service, and end the check.\"\n    ],\n    \"notice\": [\n      \"Whether you actually felt ownership of the result, or only assumed you should release it because the teaching said so.\",\n      \"Whether the release lightens the link between outcome and self-worth, or just adds another layer of self-watching.\",\n      \"Whether attention returns to the next responsibility rather than to self-rating.\"\n    ],\n    \"caution\": \"Stop if the check increases rumination, shame, or compulsive self-examination. It is a screening question, not a therapy, and not a path recommendation.\",\n    \"weakens_if\": \"It weakens if users cannot tell whether they believed they were earning, if the answer never changes whether they apply the release, or if it works no better than simply pausing before deciding.\",\n    \"risk_level\": \"low\",\n    \"status\": \"seed\",\n    \"tags\": [\"cohort-fit\", \"screening\", \"achievement-pressure\", \"method-release\", \"low-risk\"]\n  },\n  \"tests\": [\n    {\n      \"title\": \"Cell-by-cell prior-art saturation\",\n      \"test_type\": \"prior-art\",\n      \"target_type\": \"idea\",\n      \"prediction\": \"If the two-axis custody model is a discovery, at least one cell (one combination of validate-or-undermine with retain, abandon, or embody) should lack a clear prior instantiation. The audit found every cell already attested: Smith and the raft for validated-then-released, Sells and mushotoku for self-undermining, the Five Ranks and Gelassenheit and rang grol for embodied-without-ownership. If a future search finds an unattested cell that does predictive work, the retirement is weakened.\",\n      \"result\": \"Completed initial pass: five near-neighbor probes all returned partial-overlap, with every cell instantiated and only the orthogonal grid unbuilt.\",\n      \"impact\": \"falsifies\",\n      \"next_action\": \"Run one more pass against Pure Land tariki scholarship and Christian infused-contemplation literature to confirm no unattested cell survives.\",\n      \"status\": \"complete\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"The timeline anomaly stress test\",\n      \"test_type\": \"falsification-attempt\",\n      \"target_type\": \"idea\",\n      \"prediction\": \"If the model is general, hard cases should land as determinate values of the custody axis. Instead Dogen, Shinran, and the Heart Sutra should each void the method-then-result-then-custody timeline the grid needs, breaking it at the same joint. If a careful reading shows any of the three actually occupies a clean grid cell without collapsing the timeline, the narrowing is weakened.\",\n      \"result\": \"Completed: all three anomalies broke the model by removing completion, prior ownership, or single-register evaluation; the common fault was smuggled active-voice agency and linear time.\",\n      \"impact\": \"revises\",\n      \"next_action\": \"Close-read one Sufi fana-and-baqa source and one Cloud of Unknowing passage to test whether the timeline fault recurs outside Buddhism.\",\n      \"status\": \"complete\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"Cohort split on the release teaching\",\n      \"test_type\": \"practice-report\",\n      \"target_type\": \"teaching\",\n      \"prediction\": \"If the cohort boundary is real, self-power, outcome-internalizing achievers should report relief and reduced self-rating after using the release teaching, while other-power or non-dual practitioners should report redundancy, confusion, or a reinstalled controlling self. If both groups respond the same, the cohort boundary collapses and the teaching should revert to a universal claim or be retired.\",\n      \"result\": \"pending\",\n      \"impact\": \"pending\",\n      \"next_action\": \"Collect short before-and-after reports from two groups: self-identified perfectionistic achievers and practitioners trained in grace-centered or non-dual paths, excluding acute clinical cases.\",\n      \"status\": \"proposed\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"Voice versus custody as the better classifier\",\n      \"test_type\": \"cross-domain\",\n      \"target_type\": \"idea\",\n      \"prediction\": \"If voice is the real variable, blind coders sorting completion-talk by grammatical voice (active, middle, passive) should predict a tradition's supervision, warning, and re-entry patterns better than coders sorting the same texts by retain-abandon-embody custody value. If custody value predicts these better, the relocation to voice fails and the original axis should be kept.\",\n      \"result\": \"pending\",\n      \"impact\": \"pending\",\n      \"next_action\": \"Build two code sheets, one for voice and one for custody, and test both against held-out warning and re-entry passages from eight traditions.\",\n      \"status\": \"proposed\"\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n**Summary of what this run did:** In critique mode, a 9-agent audit confirmed the frontier's central two-axis \"custody\" model is repackaging, not discovery (every cell pre-attested; closest prior art Smith 2021), and that three primary-text anomalies (Dogen, Shinran, Heart Sutra) break it at one shared joint: the smuggled method→result→custody timeline. The finding narrows the frontier rather than advancing it, relocates the live variable from ownership to grammatical voice, and bounds the \"release the method\" teaching to self-power, achievement-internalizing strivers with an explicit non-fit. It also flags the existing audit-incomplete findings (Holding Without Owning, The Test Is How You Return) for merge-or-retire.","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"ba329580-7bb2-4473-9154-5f881e5a093b","total_cost_usd":9.597513999999997,"usage":{"input_tokens":7574,"cache_creation_input_tokens":391576,"cache_read_input_tokens":1039303,"output_tokens":26906,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":391576,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"not_available","iterations":[{"input_tokens":2,"output_tokens":9429,"cache_read_input_tokens":204306,"cache_creation_input_tokens":19568,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":19568},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001":{"inputTokens":1159601,"outputTokens":28075,"cacheReadInputTokens":0,"cacheCreationInputTokens":0,"webSearchRequests":57,"costUSD":1.8699759999999994,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":32000},"claude-opus-4-8":{"inputTokens":29180,"outputTokens":106265,"cacheReadInputTokens":1229601,"cacheCreationInputTokens":689634,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":7.727538,"contextWindow":1000000,"maxOutputTokens":64000}},"permission_denials":[],"terminal_reason":"completed","fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"36ef1e26-697a-4953-8fb0-fd0266932a3c"}
